  "contentHtml": "\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <p><img src=\"https://health.economictimes.indiatimes.com/Themes/Release/theme4/images/icons/et-default-user.svg\" alt=\"Online Bureau\">\n                                            \n                                        </p>\n                                                                        \n                                                                                    <ul>\n                                                                                                    <li>\n                                                                                                                                                                            <a>Online Bureau</a>\n                                                            \n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n                                                                                                            </li>\n                                                                                                                                                    <li><a href=\"/agency/88675629/ETHealthWorld\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ETHealthWorld</a></li>\n                                                                                            </ul>\n                                                                                <ul>\n                                                                                            <li>Published On May 19, 2026 at 12:37 PM IST</li>\n                                                                                                                                            <li>\n                                                        \n                                                            \n                                                                Read by \n                                                            \n                                                            100 Professionals\n                                                        \n                                                    </li>\n                                                                                    </ul>\n                                    \n                                                                            \n                                                                        \n                                \n                                \n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Mumbai: MedGenome has acquired a majority stake in Mumbai-based imaging network Siddhi Diagnostics &amp; Research Centre (SDRC), combining its genomics and multi-omics capabilities with SDRC’s three decades of <a href=\"/tag/diagnostic+imaging+expertise\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">diagnostic imaging expertise</a> to expand access to integrated diagnostic services across Western India.Founded in 1995, SDRC is led by Ajit Pungavkar and Sona Pungavkar. The network operates five centres across Nalasopara (East and West), Vasai, Virar and Thane, offering services including MRI, CT, X-ray, sonography, mammography and cardiac investigations. The promoters will continue to lead operations.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>Surajit Chakrabartty, CFO, MedGenome, said the partnership aims to combine structural insights from imaging with molecular insights from genomics to support earlier and more precise clinical decisions, while strengthening access to <a href=\"/tag/advanced+diagnostics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">advanced diagnostics</a> in high-growth suburban markets around Mumbai.Dr Pungavkar said, “In clinical practice, we often see cases where imaging alone does not provide the full picture, especially in complex or early-stage conditions. Through this partnership, we are now able to complement imaging findings with deeper molecular insights, which can significantly improve how clinicians interpret and act on diagnostic information. This brings a meaningful shift in how diagnostics are used—not just in identifying disease, but in guiding more precise and timely treatment decisions.”</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>Dr Sona added, “As diagnostics continues to evolve, the ability to integrate different layers of information becomes increasingly important. With the advancements in AI, today we are able to analyse the results of every evaluation holistically. Over time, this approach will help make advanced diagnostics more seamlessly integrated into routine care, improving both accessibility and the overall quality of <a href=\"/tag/clinical+decision-making\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">clinical decision-making</a>.”</p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                                                            <!-- <li>By <span>Online Bureau</span>,</li> -->\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <li>By\n                                                                                            <a>Online Bureau</a>\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                        , \n                                                                                    </li>\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/88675629/ETHealthWorld\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ETHealthWorld</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> Updated On May 19, 2026 at 12:37 PM IST</li> -->\n                                    <li>Published On May 19, 2026 at 12:37 PM IST</li>\n                                    <!-- <li class=\"desktop-view\">1 min read</li> -->\n                                </ul>\n                            \n                                        \n\n                    \n\n                    <!-- Comment Section -->\n                                            \n                                        <!-- Comment Section -->\n\n                    \n                      \n    \n            <p>\n                </p><h2>Join the community of 2M+ industry professionals. </h2>   \n                <h3>Subscribe to Newsletter to get latest insights &amp; analysis in your inbox.</h3>\n            <p></p>\n\n            <!-- <figure class=\"top-newsletter-subs__icon-nl\" role=\"presentation\" aria-label=\"Newsletter icon\">\n                <img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://st.etb2bimg.com/Themes/Release/theme4/images/icons/icon-newsletter.svg\" alt=\"Newsletter icon\" width=\"55\" height=\"55\">\n            </figure> -->\n        \n            \n                \n                    <h2>All about ETHealthworld industry right on your smartphone! </h2>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li><a href=\"/app\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"n